      "content": "The target isn't gone until the *last* microbe is dead, and stopping early is the fastest way to invite a relapse. If you stop now, you're just training the remaining bacteria to become resistant, which is a far greater long-term health risk than finishing the course. For maximum efficiency, take the full ten days as prescribed, and if you want to boost your recovery, start taking a high-quality, broad-spectrum probiotic immediately.",
